      <p>Apply for, check and update goods or public service vehicle (PSV) operator’s licences online. You’ll need to <a href="create-account.html">create an account</a> first before you can start using the service.</p>
      <p>This service replaces the VOSA Self Service system. You can still log in to your existing Self Service account using your current username and password through the new service.</p>
      <div class="actions-container">
        <a class="action--primary large" href="sign-in.html">Start now</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article">
      <h3>Before you start</h3>
      <p>Before you create an account and apply for your first licence, ensure that you have read up on the legal obligations of being either a <a href="">goods</a> or <a href="">public service vehicle</a> operator.</p>
      <p>Once you have created an account you’ll be sent a temporary password to your email address. You can then start using the online service.</p><br />
      <h3>What you can do</h3>
      <p>You can:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>update your existing licence and application details</li>
        <li>apply for new licences</li>
        <li>check the status of your current applications</li>
        <li>pay licence fees</li>
        <li>add or remove vehicles</li>
        <li>order duplicate operator licence discs</li>
        <li>manage your bus registrations (PSV only)</li>
      </ul>
